# HTML Structure and Semantic Guidelines

This document defines the HTML coding standards for semantic markup, partials usage, accessibility, and proper document structure.

## 1. Document Structure and Formatting

Always use semantic HTML5 markup with proper document structure.

### Good Example (Correct)
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  @include('partials/head.html')
</head>
<body>
  <div class="site">
    @include('partials/header.html')
    <main>
      <div class="container">
        <!-- Page content -->
      </div>
    </main>
    @include('partials/footer.html')
  </div>
  @include('partials/script.html')
</body>
</html>
```

### Bad Example (Incorrect)
```html
<!-- Missing DOCTYPE, wrong language, no semantic structure -->
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
  <div>
    <!-- Content without semantic tags -->
  </div>
</body>
</html>
```

## 2. Working with Partials

Partials allow for modular HTML organization and reusability across pages.

### Partials Structure
- Store partials in `src/partials/` folder
- Main partials: `head.html`, `header.html`, `footer.html`, `form.html`, `script.html`
- Use descriptive filenames

### Including Partials
```html
<!-- Use this syntax for including partials -->
@include('partials/filename.html')

<!-- In <head> section -->
@include('partials/head.html')

<!-- In <body> section -->
@include('partials/header.html')
@include('partials/footer.html')
@include('partials/script.html')
```

## 3. Semantic HTML5 Tags

Use semantic tags to create meaningful document structure.

### Good Example (Correct)
```html
<header class="header">
  <nav class="nav">
    <!-- Navigation content -->
  </nav>
</header>

<main class="main">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1 class="hero-title">Page Title</h1>
  </section>
  
  <section class="content">
    <article class="article">
      <!-- Article content -->
    </article>
  </section>
</main>

<footer class="footer">
  <!-- Footer content -->
</footer>
```

### Bad Example (Incorrect)
```html
<!-- Using only divs without semantic meaning -->
<div class="header">
  <div class="nav">
    <!-- Navigation content -->
  </div>
</div>

<div class="main">
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-title">Page Title</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## 4. Accessibility (A11y)

Ensure your HTML is accessible to all users and assistive technologies.

### Required Attributes
- Add `alt` attributes for all images
- Use `aria-label` for navigation buttons
- Add proper `name` attributes for form fields
- Use `.visually-hidden` class for screen reader text

### Good Example (Correct)
```html
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Descriptive image text">

<button class="menu-toggle" aria-label="Toggle navigation menu">
  <span class="visually-hidden">Menu</span>
</button>

<input type="text" name="username" id="username" aria-label="Username">
```

## 5. Forms Structure

Use consistent form structure with proper labeling and organization.

### Good Example (Correct)
```html
<form class="form">
  <div class="form-group">
    <label class="form-label" for="email">Email</label>
    <input class="form-input" type="email" name="email" id="email">
  </div>
  
  <div class="form-group">
    <label class="form-label" for="message">Message</label>
    <textarea class="form-input" name="message" id="message"></textarea>
  </div>
  
  <button class="btn btn--primary" type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
```

### Bad Example (Incorrect)
```html
<!-- Missing labels, poor structure -->
<form>
  <input type="email" placeholder="Email">
  <textarea placeholder="Message"></textarea>
  <button>Submit</button>
</form>
```

## 6. Meta Tags and Head Section

Include essential meta tags for proper document behavior and SEO.

```html
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow">
  
  <!-- Preconnect for performance -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  
  <!-- Stylesheets -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css">
</head>
```

## 7. Multi-page Structure

Maintain consistency across multiple pages by following these guidelines:

1. Copy `index.html` to create new pages
2. Rename files according to content purpose
3. Use the same structural approach for all pages
4. Keep partials consistent across pages
